{
  "texts": [
    "The most adopted approach is Support Vector Machine (SVM) (Hearst et al. 1998), which aligns with the findings of prior studies (Schmidt et al. 2021).",
    "Four of the tools (Abstractr, FAST2, Rayyan, RobotAnalyst) exclusively rely on SVM.",
    "Distiller supports both SVM and Naive Bayes.",
    "ASReview allows the user to select a vast range of methods, including Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Naive Bayes, SVM, and a Neural Networks classifier.",
    "Litsuggest use logistic regression, while SWIFT-Review and SWIFT-Active Screener use a method based on log-lineal regression."
  ]
}